If $AAPL is exploring Starlink for iPhone it confirms satellite connectivity is becoming a standard feature in smartphones.

Starlink can support messaging & basic apps but it is important to call out that $ASTS is building full broadband to unmodified devices (voice, data, video) which is why carriers like $T, $VZ, Vodafone & Rakuten are aligned with AST.

They want global coverage & they want to keep the mobile customer relationship without handing it to a fixed broadband competitor.

A Starlink + iPhone partnership will most likely shift FUD around AST in the near term but my takeaway is that it does not replace the need for real mobile broadband from space in places towers cannot reach.

Both can win but only one delivers the full phone experience everywhere on Earth.
